Public administration concerns policy formulation and implementation and management of public affairs by competent civil servants who constitute public services or civil services. Public administration is essential for executing government orders and functions. A whole range of new career opportunities can be taken up in this sector.

Public administration is the implementation of government policy and also an academic discipline that studies this implementation and prepares civil servants for working in the public service. Public administration concerns policy formulation and implementation and management of public affairs by competent civil servants who constitute public services or civil services. Public administration is essential for executing government orders and functions.The civil service is the backbone of the administrative system of the country. Civil Services of India can be classified into two types - the All India Services and the Central Civil Services (Group A and B). The recruits are university graduates (or above) selected through a rigorous system of examinations, called the Civil Services Examination (CSE) conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC). Law related careers involve study, development and application of law.

The person with social interest is classified as helper. Helping jobs involve assisting, teaching, coaching, and serving other people. Helpers like working in cooperative environments to improve the lives of others. A person is classified as a Helper when he or she is mostly interested in jobs that help or serve other people (Social interest). Helpers are typically compassionate, caring people who like to see the impact of their work on others lives. Helpers often choose careers in health care, social service, counseling, human resources and personal care. Helpers like working closely with others in a way that allows you to make a positive impact on their lives. They like enjoy teaching, counseling, and caring for other people. Choosing work that allows you to live out your personal values is very important to you. Most Helpers dislike working alone. They place a high value on their relationships and want to work in cooperation and harmony with others.

Interests refer to an individual’s preference for engaging in one or more speciﬁc activities relative to others. It involves the activities that excites and gives you enjoyment, including what you like to watch, shows you like to attend, and the kind of people you admire and like to be with. Interests reﬂect a person’s preferences, attitudes, values, talents, and qualities. Interest is important in choosing a career because interest keeps you motivated and engaged in your work. Since you spend most of your time during a day and week at the workplace; if you have no interest in what you are doing, it can adversely aﬀect your personal life.

Skill ﬁnder test is designed to identify your interests and multiple intelligence. It will help you to ﬁnd the skills already developed in you and to identify the skills to be developed based on your interests. This test report will map out your interest areas and multiple intelligences and provide you with suggestions on which career ﬁeld you can ﬂourish.

Personality is a characteristic way of behaving. It includes behavioural characteristics, both inherent and acquired, that distinguish one person from another and that can be observed in people’s relations to the environment and to the social group.
DESCRIPTION OF YOUR TYPES OF INTELLIGENCE

An aptitude is a component of a competence to do a certain kind of work at a certain level. Outstanding aptitude can be considered "talent". An aptitude may be physical or mental. It is an inborn potential to do certain kinds of work whether developed or undeveloped. Aptitude tests are designed to assess your thinking performance.

Right Career Finder test is designed to identify the right career that fit for you on the basis of your interest area, aptitude, personality type, multiple intelligence, career motivators, skills, knowledge, etc. Selecting right career is very important as you are going to spend a major part of your life for this career. This test will help you, to make decision on right career from a large number of career options before you and to select the skill improvement programs to be attended to make a good career growth.

Description of Your Types of Intelligence

People with intrapersonal intelligence are skilled at looking inward and figuring out their own feelings, strengths, weakness, motivations and goals. They are introspective and seek understanding. They are intuitive and typically introverted. Planning of own life gets easier due to accurate perception of own inner abilities. This is referred as private intelligence as nobody can detect totally.
